http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Visual Art Curriculum Standards for 5th grade.
Media, Techniques, and Processes - Students will understand and apply media, techniques, and processes.
Manipulate a variety of tools and media in a safe and responsible manner.
Apply a variety of media.
Analyze and demonstrate a variety of techniques.
Analyze and apply a variety of processes.
Recognize, demonstrate and evaluate levels of craftsmanship.
Structures and Functions - Students will use knowledge of structures and functions.
Analyze and apply the elements of art.
Apply the elements of art.
Analyze and apply principles of design.
Apply principles of design.
Evaluate purpose in art.
Apply purpose in art.
Evaluate context in art.
Apply context in art.
Evaluation - Students will choose and evaluate a range of subject matter, symbols, and ideas.
Plan, design, and demonstrate subject matter, symbols, and ideas in one's art.
Analyze and critique subject matter, symbols, and ideas in one's art.
Critique subject matter, symbols, and ideas in art.
Historical and Cultural Relationships - Students will understand the visual arts in relation to history and cultures.
Explore the relationship of art from different cultures, time, and places.
Examine and demonstrate how culture, history, and art influence each other.
Reflecting and Assessing - The student will reflect upon and assess the characteristics and merits of their work and the work of others.
Analyze and justify the characteristics and merits of one's artwork.
Analyze and justify the characteristics and merits of other's artwork.
Investigate and evaluate viewers' responses to art.
Interdisciplinary Connections - Students will make connections between visual arts and other disciplines.
Compare and analyze connections between visual arts and other arts disciplines.
Compare and analyze connections between visual arts and disciplines outside the arts.
